## Part 1: Age

### Examiner

**Are you happy to be the age you are now? Why/Why not?**

### Candidate

Yes, I am, actually. I think the age I am now is a really interesting stage of life, because I’m old enough to make my own decisions, but still young enough to keep learning, experimenting, and changing direction if I want to. I feel that at this age, I have a bit more maturity than I did a few years ago, so I can think more clearly about my future. At the same time, I still have plenty of energy and ambition, which is something I really value.

### 翻译

是的，我其实挺满意自己现在这个年龄的。
我觉得现在这个人生阶段很有意思，因为我已经足够成熟，可以自己做决定，但同时又足够年轻，还可以继续学习、尝试新事物，甚至如果我想的话，还能改变人生方向。
我觉得和几年前相比，我现在更成熟了一些，所以能更清楚地思考自己的未来。
与此同时，我也仍然有很多精力和抱负，而这是我非常珍惜的一点。

---

### Examiner

**When you were a child, did you think a lot about your future? Why/Why not?**

### Candidate

Yes, I did, although my ideas were quite simple at that time. When I was a child, I often imagined what kind of job I might have or what kind of life I would live as an adult. I think children naturally feel curious about the future, especially when they are asked questions like “What do you want to be when you grow up?” In my case, I probably didn’t think about it in a very practical way, but I definitely liked imagining different possibilities, and that gave me motivation to study and improve myself.

### 翻译

是的，我小时候确实会经常想未来，不过那时候的想法比较简单。
小时候，我经常会想自己将来会做什么工作，或者长大后会过怎样的生活。
我觉得孩子天生就会对未来感到好奇，尤其是当大人经常问“你长大后想做什么”这种问题时。
对我来说，那时候我可能并不是很实际地去思考未来，但我确实很喜欢想象各种可能性，而这也给了我学习和提升自己的动力。

---

### Examiner

**Do you think you have changed as you have got older? Why/Why not?**

### Candidate

Yes, definitely. I think I’ve become much more patient and realistic as I’ve grown older. When I was younger, I tended to focus more on immediate feelings or short-term results, but now I pay more attention to long-term goals and personal development. I also think I’ve become better at understanding other people’s perspectives, which makes me more thoughtful in communication. So overall, I’d say getting older has made me more mature, both in the way I think and in the way I deal with challenges.

### 翻译

是的，当然。
我觉得随着年龄增长，我变得更有耐心，也更现实了。
小时候或者更年轻的时候，我更容易关注当下的感受或者短期结果，但现在我会更关注长期目标和个人成长。
我也觉得自己更能理解别人的观点了，这让我在人际沟通中更周到。
所以总体来说，我会认为长大让我变得更成熟了，不管是在思维方式上，还是在面对困难的方式上。

---

### Examiner

**What will be different about your life in the future? Why?**

### Candidate

I think my life will probably become more structured and more responsibility-based in the future. At the moment, a large part of my life is centered around studying and preparing for the next stage, but in the future I’ll most likely be working full-time and making more independent decisions. I also hope I’ll become financially independent, which will give me greater freedom but also more pressure. So I expect my future life to be busier and more demanding, but hopefully also more meaningful, because I’ll be moving closer to the kind of life I want to build.

### 翻译

我觉得未来我的生活可能会变得更有条理，也会围绕更多责任展开。
目前，我生活中很大一部分都集中在学习和为下一个阶段做准备，但将来我很可能会全职工作，并做出更多独立决定。
我也希望自己能实现经济独立，这会给我更大的自由，但同时也会带来更多压力。
所以我预计未来的生活会更忙、更有挑战性，但也希望会更有意义，因为那意味着我正在一步步接近自己想建立的人生。

