## Part 3

### Technology and education

---

### Examiner

**What is the best age for children to start computer lessons?**

### Candidate

I think children can start learning basic computer skills at quite a young age, probably in primary school. At that stage, they are usually curious and quick to pick up new things, so it’s a good time to introduce simple digital skills such as typing, searching for information, or using educational software. However, I don’t think the focus should be on advanced technical knowledge too early. What matters more is helping them become comfortable and responsible users of technology. In my opinion, a balanced and age-appropriate introduction is much better than pushing children too hard from the beginning.

### 翻译

我觉得孩子可以在比较小的时候开始学习基础电脑技能，大概小学阶段就可以了。
在那个阶段，他们通常很好奇，也很容易学会新东西，所以是引入一些简单数字技能的好时机，比如打字、查找信息，或者使用教育软件。
不过，我不认为应该过早把重点放在高级技术知识上。
更重要的是帮助他们成为能够熟练且负责任地使用科技的人。
在我看来，循序渐进、适合年龄的引导，比一开始就给孩子太大压力要好得多。

---

### Examiner

**Do you think schools should use more technology to help children learn?**

### Candidate

Yes, to a certain extent, I do. I think technology can make learning more interactive, efficient, and engaging. For example, with videos, digital exercises, and online resources, students can often understand difficult ideas more easily than through traditional methods alone. Technology can also give students access to a much wider range of information. That said, I don’t think it should completely replace conventional teaching. If schools rely on it too heavily, students may become distracted or less able to concentrate. So I’d say technology should be used as a support tool rather than as a complete substitute for teachers or textbooks.

### 翻译

是的，在一定程度上我同意。
我认为科技可以让学习变得更有互动性、更高效，也更吸引人。
例如，通过视频、数字练习和网络资源，学生往往能比单靠传统教学更容易理解一些难点。
科技也可以让学生接触到更广泛的信息。
不过，我不认为它应该完全取代传统教学。
如果学校过度依赖科技，学生可能会更容易分心，或者专注力变差。
所以我会说，科技应该被当作一种辅助工具，而不是教师或教材的完全替代品。

---

### Examiner

**Do you agree or disagree that computers will replace teachers one day?**

### Candidate

I disagree with that idea, at least in the full sense of the word “replace.” Computers can certainly support teaching in many ways. They can provide information quickly, personalize learning tasks, and help students practise at their own pace. However, teachers do much more than simply deliver knowledge. They guide students, understand their emotions, encourage them, and adjust their teaching depending on the needs of the class. Those human qualities are very difficult for computers to fully reproduce. So in my view, technology will become more important in education, but teachers will still remain essential.

### 翻译

我不同意这个观点，至少如果“取代”是完全意义上的话，我并不同意。
电脑当然可以在很多方面支持教学。
它们可以快速提供信息、个性化学习任务，也能帮助学生按照自己的节奏练习。
然而，老师做的事情远不只是传授知识。
他们会引导学生、理解学生情绪、鼓励他们，并根据班级需要调整教学方式。
这些人类特有的特质，很难被电脑完全复制。
所以在我看来，科技在教育中的重要性会越来越高，但老师依然是不可或缺的。

---

### Technology and society

---

### Examiner

**How much has technology improved how we communicate with each other?**

### Candidate

I think technology has improved communication enormously. In the past, people had to wait much longer to contact someone, especially if that person lived far away. Nowadays, we can send messages instantly, make video calls, and share information in real time, which has made communication much faster and more convenient. Technology has also made it easier to maintain relationships across long distances. However, I do think there is a downside. Sometimes online communication can feel less personal, and people may rely on it so much that they communicate less effectively face to face. So overall, the improvement has been huge, but it has also brought some challenges.

### 翻译

我认为科技极大地改善了人与人之间的沟通。
过去，人们联系别人往往要等很久，尤其是当对方住得很远的时候。
如今，我们可以即时发消息、打视频电话，并实时分享信息，这让沟通变得更快也更方便。
科技也让维持远距离关系变得更容易。
不过，我确实觉得它也有负面影响。
有时候线上交流会显得不够有人情味，而且人们可能过度依赖它，导致面对面沟通能力下降。
所以总体来说，这种改善是巨大的，但同时也带来了一些挑战。

---

### Examiner

**Do you agree that there are still many more major technological innovations to be made?**

### Candidate

Yes, absolutely. Although technology has already advanced very rapidly, I believe we are still far from reaching the limit of what is possible. There are many areas that still need major breakthroughs, such as medicine, clean energy, transportation, and artificial intelligence. For instance, if technology can help us cure serious diseases more effectively or reduce environmental damage, that would have an enormous impact on society. I also think human needs keep changing, so innovation will continue naturally. In other words, as long as new problems appear, there will always be room for major technological progress.

### 翻译

是的，当然同意。
虽然科技已经发展得非常快了，但我认为我们离“极限”还很远。
在很多领域仍然需要重大突破，比如医学、清洁能源、交通以及人工智能。
例如，如果科技能帮助我们更有效地治疗重大疾病，或者减少环境破坏，那将对社会产生巨大的影响。
我也认为人类的需求一直在变化，所以创新自然会持续发生。
换句话说，只要新的问题不断出现，就永远会有重大科技进步的空间。

---

### Examiner

**Could you suggest some reasons why some people are deciding to reduce their use of technology?**

### Candidate

Yes, I think there are several reasons for that. One major reason is that many people feel overwhelmed by constant notifications, online information, and social media pressure. As a result, they may become mentally tired or feel that they can never truly relax. Another reason is that some people are worried about privacy and how much of their personal data is being collected. In addition, others simply want a healthier lifestyle, with more face-to-face interaction, better sleep, and less screen time. So I think reducing technology use is often an attempt to regain control over one’s time, attention, and well-being.

### 翻译

可以，我觉得这背后有几个原因。
一个主要原因是，很多人会被不断弹出的通知、海量网络信息以及社交媒体压力弄得身心俱疲。
结果就是，他们可能会感到精神疲惫，或者觉得自己永远无法真正放松。
另一个原因是，有些人担心隐私问题，以及自己的个人数据被收集了多少。
此外，还有一些人只是想要一种更健康的生活方式，比如更多面对面交流、更好的睡眠，以及更少的屏幕时间。
所以我认为，减少使用科技，往往是在试图重新掌控自己的时间、注意力和身心状态。

